      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(EmployeeInfo other)
        Compare this EmployeeInfo object and other EmployeeInfo object. An EmployeeInfo 'info1' is "smaller" than another 'info2' if info1's salary is higher than info2's. If both have the same salary, then one with a larger department id is considered as "smaller". When being sorted in an increasing order (using Arrays.sort), the smaller EmployeeInfo object appears earlier than the larger one.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<EmployeeInfo>
        Returns:
        Positive value if this is larger than other, negative if this is smaller than other, zero otherwise.
